==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Electroscope
<hw>E*lec"tro*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Electro-</ets> + <ets>-scope</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧lectroscope</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An
instrument for detecting the presence of electricity, or changes in the
electric state of bodies, or the species of electricity present, as by
means of pith balls, and the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Condensing electroscope</b></col> <fld>(Physics)</fld>,
<cd>a form of electroscope in which an increase of sensibility is
obtained by the use of a condenser.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electroscopic</ent>⟦br⟧
